</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> No the only reason it has turned into that was because you

<BR>&gt; posted a response to my message flaming me. You started this
<BR>&gt; stupid little war not me. I was using a specific example to get
<BR>&gt; my point across. It was you that started this UO your character
<BR>&gt; is better than my character war not me.
<P>i played UO for like, 10minutes total.....why would i propose to talk trash about a character i never had in a game i never played???.....think about it, bright boy
<P>&gt; How can you say in any way what verant wants, you have no idea
<BR>&gt; what varant wants. If having a free PVP environment makes EQ a
<BR>&gt; better game then maybe thats what verant wants. You have no say
<BR>&gt; in deciding this it is completely up to verant.
<P>because i was in the beta long enough to have been there for all the major decisions Verant made regarding PvP....i've read enough Brad mandates on the subject to have a pretty good idea of their feelings on the subject.....in fact, i'm pretty sure this board, geiger, and the PvP server exist because enough UO rejects were whining that Verant had to shovel them off somewhere so they could work on developing the game for the people they initially began developing the game for....and i got news for ya, it ain't us........i'm kinda stuck in the middle here, i like PvP and think it's a benefit to the game...but on the other hand, i'm none too happy about having to share server space with players like you (i'm not a fan of unrestricted PvP)....so why can't u UO guys respect the opinions of people who don't dig your style of gameplay?....not everyone wants to play EverQuake....certainly there is a happy medium if you guys would let someone find it
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
